sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Spark Operator Controller<br/>8080/TCP metrics
    participant SparkSubmit as spark-submit<br/>(in-process)
    participant Driver as Driver Pod<br/>7078/TCP, 7079/TCP
    participant Executors as Executor Pods
    participant ConnectSvc as SparkConnect Service<br/>15002/TCP gRPC

    note over User,Executors: Flow 1: SparkApplication Submission and Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. Create SparkApplication CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | Bearer token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 2. Admission review (validate + mutate)<br/>HTTPS/9443 | API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validated + mutated SparkApplication
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: 3. Watch event: new SparkApplication
    Controller->>SparkSubmit: 4. Exec spark-submit (in-process)
    SparkSubmit->>K8sAPI: 5. Create driver pod<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 6. Mutate driver pod (26-step pipeline)<br/>HTTPS/9443 | API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated driver pod (env, volumes, scheduling, monitoring)
    K8sAPI-->>Driver: Driver pod scheduled
    Driver->>K8sAPI: 7. Create executor pods<br/>HTTPS/443 | spark-operator-spark SA token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 8. Mutate executor pods (26-step pipeline)<br/>HTTPS/9443 | API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated executor pods
    K8sAPI-->>Executors: Executor pods scheduled
    Executors->>Driver: 9. RPC connection<br/>TCP/7078 | No encryption
    Executors->>Driver: 10. BlockManager data<br/>TCP/7079 | No encryption
    Driver-->>Controller: Pod status events
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update SparkApplication status

    note over User,Executors: Flow 2: ScheduledSparkApplication Cron Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: Create ScheduledSparkApplication CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | Bearer token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch event: new ScheduledSparkApplication
    Controller->>Controller: 1. Cron evaluation (in-process)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 2. Create child SparkApplication CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token
    note right of Controller: Triggers Flow 1 (steps 3-10)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4. Delete old SparkApp CRs<br/>(per history limits)<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token

    note over User,ConnectSvc: Flow 3: SparkConnect Server Lifecycle

    User->>K8sAPI: Create SparkConnect CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | Bearer token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch event: new SparkConnect
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 1. Create ConfigMap (executor template)<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 2. Create server pod<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 3. Create Service (4 ports:<br/>7078, 7079, 4040, 15002)<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token
    User->>ConnectSvc: 4. Connect to SparkConnect<br/>gRPC/15002 | No encryption
    ConnectSvc->>K8sAPI: 5. Create executor pods<br/>(dynamic allocation)<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA token
